      "role": "user",
      "content": "i mean, i get the \"mix of solutions\" thing, but it feels like people who say we can just use batteries and renewables alone are being a bit unrealistic given how fast we need to decarbonize. if we don't start building more reactors now, aren't we basically just guaranteeing we'll miss the targets? isn't it kind of irresponsible to treat nuclear like it's just one \"optional\" thing on the list?",
